data.text:
PARENT 12 Dorothea Elizabeth Irving 1904 [1455]

SIR JOHN HENRY KILIAN BRUNNER 4TH BARONET was born on the 1 June 1927.

He married JASMINE CECILY WARDROP-MOORE on the 22 December 1955.

John Brunner was educated at Eton College, Eton, Berkshire, England. He gained the rank of Lieutenant in the service of the Royal Artillery. He graduated from Trinity College, Oxford University, Oxford, Oxfordshire, England, in 1950 with a Bachelor of Arts (B.A.) ). He was with PEP (later to became PSI) between 1950 and 1953.

John was a talks producer in 1953 and was an economics advisor to Treasury between 1958 and 1961. He was assistant manager of the Observer in 1961.

John succeeded to the title of 4th Baronet Brunner [U.K., 1895] in 1982. In 2003 he was living at 138 Victoria Avenue, Dalkeith, Western Australia, Australia.
